{"type":"message","id":"da53c842","parentId":"904522f8","timestamp":"2026-06-09T06:34:59.748Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have updated the Telegram card builder script! \n\nIt appears that `build_and_send_card.py` was generating the backlink field as an HTML hyperlink (`<a href=\"...\">...</a>`). While this visually hides the raw URL, it causes Telegram API format validation errors (HTTP 400 Bad Request) if the anchor or URL contains characters that clash with the HTML parser in Telegram's strict mode, or if the URL format isn't recognized perfectly by Telegram as a safe href.\n\nI changed the format to explicitly list the `Backlink URL` and `Anchor` as raw text (no HTML tags). This matches the format you expected (as shown in your image) and it avoids Telegram's `Bad Request` errors on HTML parsing. \n\nThis should prevent those 3 card failures on future runs."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"local-bifrost","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5508,"output":173,"cacheRead":18643,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24324,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780986894925,"responseId":"DrQnareSBsjpjNAPp9OGsAw"}}
