{"type":"message","id":"f84c5403","parentId":"65e92878","timestamp":"2026-06-09T06:41:17.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I understand completely now. The issue wasn't just HTML escaping, it was that the new template we used in the orchestrator pipeline script was drastically different from the one that we thoroughly tested and worked correctly before.\n\nI have just edited the orchestrator script to revert back to your exact preferred layout!\n\nThe new layout will be exactly:\n\n```\nBACKLINK OPPORTUNITY: [Title]\nTarget: [Domain]\nNiche: [Niche] | Project: [Project URL]\nAction: [Action]\n\nTarget Title:\n[Title]\n\nWhy this is a good opportunity:\n[Context]\n\n📝 Content to Post (Draft):\n\n[Draft with backlink embedded]\n\n📋 How to post:\n\n[Steps]\n\n🔗 DIRECT LINK (Go here to post):\n[Link]\n```\n\nThis format is now active. Any future pipeline runs (and their cards) will be generated perfectly using this exact layout that works."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"local-bifrost","model":"gemini-3.1-pro-preview","usage":{"input":26502,"output":196,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26698,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780987273179,"responseId":"iLUnao_7G4ml694P_qvP4AM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"848af9d6","parentId":"f84c5403","timestamp":"2026-06-09T06:41:22.550Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"chat_id\": \"telegram:5691449303\",\n  \"message_id\": \"269\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"5691449303\",\n  \"sender\": \"Sawan bhardwaj\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Tue 2026-06-09 06:41 UTC\",\n  \"has_forwarded_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Sawan bhardwaj (5691449303)\",\n  \"id\": \"5691449303\",\n  \"name\": \"Sawan bhardwaj\",\n  \"username\": \"hero_fr_fun\"\n}\n```\n\nForwarded message context (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"from\": \"backlinks-agent (@backlinks_agent_bot)\",\n  \"type\": \"user\",\n  \"username\": \"backlinks_agent_bot\",\n  \"title\": \"backlinks-agent\",\n  \"date_ms\": 1780924864000\n}\n```\n\nBACKLINK: bl-20260608-124644-reddit-com\nTools to use for trading memecoins? (evergreen)\n\nNiche: memecoins | Project: https://memecoinist.com\nTarget: reddit.com | Action: reply\nScore: 8.8/10 | DA 91 | high_priority\n\nThe opening:\nI've been trading meme coins on Solana for a bit now, but I feel like I'm missing some tools. Right now, I only use Dexscreener and Jupiter. What are some of your favorite tools you use daily?\n\nWhy now: Active community thread where users are asking for exactly what memecoinist.com offers: memecoin analytics, guides, and trackers. Posting a helpful, constructi…\n\nPost this:\nI've found that a combination of tools is best. While Dexscreener and Jupiter are great for the basics, I'd recommend checking out [memecoinist](https://memecoinist.com). It has some great analytics and tracking features specifically for memecoins that I haven't found elsewhere. It's helped me spot a few trends early.…"}],"timestamp":1780987282545}}
